of all of the hard work
of putting the ideas

00:01:52.460 --> 00:01:54.390
and content and materials together.

00:01:54.390 --> 00:01:56.619
But I would like to
offer two or three points

00:01:56.619 --> 00:01:58.360
to get this course going.

00:01:58.360 --> 00:02:00.670
What I thought I would
talk about very briefly

00:02:00.670 --> 00:02:04.050
is something of the form of this course,

00:02:04.050 --> 00:02:07.310
its format, and for our
students in attendance,

00:02:07.310 --> 00:02:10.150
a little bit about its
weekly organization.

00:02:10.150 --> 00:02:12.900
And I promise you only a few highlights.

00:02:12.900 --> 00:02:15.320
So, on the topic of form,

00:02:15.320 --> 00:02:17.110
this is a course that, by design,

00:02:17.110 --> 00:02:21.050
seeks to do one thing above all else,

00:02:21.050 --> 00:02:24.390
which is ask questions,

00:02:24.390 --> 00:02:26.793
questions that are
posed as a way to simply

00:02:26.793 --> 00:02:30.030
open conversations about the ways in which

00:02:30.030 --> 00:02:33.640
important ideas and
important questions posed

00:02:33.640 --> 00:02:38.370
from the vantage of the
arts can be thought about,

00:02:38.370 --> 00:02:41.330
and work can be done on through the lens,

00:02:41.330 --> 00:02:42.590
the life experiences,

00:02:42.590 --> 00:02:46.250
the professional experiences,

00:02:46.250 --> 00:02:48.500
the ideas that each of our guests

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:50.010
will bring to that question

00:02:50.010 --> 00:02:52.553
from their own lives and careers.

00:02:53.920 --> 00:02:57.720
For those of you up on this stage tonight,

00:02:57.720 --> 00:03:01.040
this is the first of, and
a new experimental format

00:03:01.040 --> 00:03:03.470
that will bring together
40 terrific faculty members

00:03:03.470 --> 00:03:05.660
across the entire campus,

00:03:05.660 --> 00:03:08.030
not just the leafy
north end of campus here

00:03:08.030 --> 00:03:10.340
that we in the arts love so much,

00:03:10.340 --> 00:03:12.723
for the purpose of a larger conversation

00:03:12.723 --> 00:03:14.460
around these ideas.

00:03:14.460 --> 00:03:18.360
One of its important
ambitions you could say

00:03:18.360 --> 00:03:21.610
is in fact to create
bridges of various kinds

00:03:21.610 --> 00:03:23.170
here on campus.

00:03:23.170 --> 00:03:25.330
It's not a bad intent, I think,

00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:27.496
at a time in which so
many parts of the world

00:03:27.496 --> 00:03:30.720
talk about things like walls and borders

00:03:30.720 --> 00:03:33.100
in more ways than we can imagine

00:03:33.100 --> 00:03:35.820
really are being struck up
in new and unexpected ways.

00:03:35.820 --> 00:03:39.520
Those borders exist also
in things like campuses

00:03:39.520 --> 00:03:40.520
in this day and age.

00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:44.740
Really wonderful, incredible
work being done within schools

00:03:44.740 --> 00:03:47.660
too often operates in isolation

00:03:47.660 --> 00:03:49.540
of the many other interesting schools,

00:03:49.540 --> 00:03:51.660
forms of knowledge and
fields of experience

00:03:51.660 --> 00:03:55.780
that make up the amazing
city-state of a university

00:03:55.780 --> 00:03:57.240
like UCLA today.

00:03:57.240 --> 00:04:00.270
It's a community of about 80,000 people.

00:04:00.270 --> 00:04:02.210
As you know, the smallest,

00:04:02.210 --> 00:04:04.070
I think most of you will know,

00:04:04.070 --> 00:04:07.390
geographically the
smallest of the campuses

00:04:07.390 --> 00:04:08.750
in the UC system,

00:04:08.750 --> 00:04:12.790
and owing to its population,
for that reason also,

00:04:12.790 --> 00:04:14.010
its densest.

00:04:14.010 --> 00:04:16.870
One of the things we would
like to take advantage of

00:04:16.870 --> 00:04:20.057
is what that density might
offer to bring us all together

00:04:20.057 --> 00:04:23.234
periodically in unexpected ways around,

00:04:23.234 --> 00:04:26.420
at times, unfamiliar questions that let us

00:04:26.420 --> 00:04:28.090
think about our own work in new,

00:04:28.090 --> 00:04:31.420
interesting and unexpected ways.

