01:13:31.290 --> 01:13:34.560
for that time when you can record data,

01:13:34.560 --> 01:13:36.110
or develop a new capability

01:13:36.110 --> 01:13:38.130
that you get to see from the outside.

01:13:38.130 --> 01:13:40.110
But, for instance, there is a microscope

01:13:40.110 --> 01:13:42.822
we've been trying to make
work for 29 years now.

01:13:42.822 --> 01:13:44.770
(laughs) And we're getting closer,

01:13:44.770 --> 01:13:47.850
but the student who was
working on it just graduated

01:13:47.850 --> 01:13:48.990
so we'll start a new PhD.

01:13:48.990 --> 01:13:50.980
You know, you learn things along the way,

01:13:50.980 --> 01:13:54.729
but we come up with a
problem we wanna solve,

01:13:54.729 --> 01:13:57.880
and then we try and
develop a tool to do that,

01:13:57.880 --> 01:14:00.160
whether it's understanding chemistry,

01:14:00.160 --> 01:14:04.800
or light coming out of
an object and so forth.

01:14:04.800 --> 01:14:05.940
I mean, one advantage...

01:14:05.940 --> 01:14:08.120
I have a very bad sense of direction.

01:14:08.120 --> 01:14:10.670
So, a nice thing about the nano scale is

01:14:10.670 --> 01:14:14.170
we make it so everything
looks the same everywhere,

01:14:14.170 --> 01:14:15.370
so you can choose any part

01:14:15.370 --> 01:14:17.040
and sort of get the statistics you need.

01:14:17.040 --> 01:14:19.990
We don't have to find the
star that does this, or...

01:14:20.980 --> 01:14:25.250
And so, we can find, you
know, here's the arrangement

01:14:26.130 --> 01:14:28.750
we wanted to see many times repeated,

01:14:28.750 --> 01:14:31.130
and then do the measurements and discover

01:14:31.130 --> 01:14:32.360
that they all behave differently,

01:14:32.360 --> 01:14:35.440
and even individuals
could change over time.

01:14:35.440 --> 01:14:36.630
So the fun comes at the end,

01:14:36.630 --> 01:14:39.750
but there's a lot of work
that goes every day, yeah.

01:14:39.750 --> 01:14:40.583
- [Brett] Rodrigo.

01:14:40.583 --> 01:14:41.853
- I mean, it's interesting being able to

01:14:41.853 --> 01:14:46.103
continually use tools
that look like the tool

01:14:46.103 --> 01:14:49.015
that is required for the job.

01:14:49.015 --> 01:14:54.015
I have to encounter a lot where
the tools I use to make art,

01:14:54.260 --> 01:14:56.420
like I spend a lot of time
in Home Depot, and I spend...

01:14:56.420 --> 01:14:58.700
All the things that you make work,

01:14:58.700 --> 01:15:03.120
they have a patina that
they are not art, right?

01:15:03.120 --> 01:15:08.120
And you conduct meaning from
things into something else.

