01:17:05.290 --> 01:17:06.680
in some way.

01:17:06.680 --> 01:17:08.200
- [Dana] It's interesting to think about

01:17:08.200 --> 01:17:11.060
whether you can construct
a work that's not finished.

01:17:11.060 --> 01:17:11.893
- Yeah.
- And I think

01:17:11.893 --> 01:17:14.820
that's not been a long
history in architecture,

01:17:14.820 --> 01:17:17.870
when you think of it having
to be somehow completed.

01:17:17.870 --> 01:17:22.050
But that project in particular
was kind of brilliant,

01:17:22.050 --> 01:17:25.597
in that it expected it to keep changing

01:17:25.597 --> 01:17:27.513
and evolving and growing.

01:17:29.191 --> 01:17:31.670
- Which is, as a comment,

01:17:31.670 --> 01:17:35.180
touches on this idea of
a space of production,

01:17:35.180 --> 01:17:36.750
or a project's reception,

01:17:36.750 --> 01:17:39.440
which I'm interested in
