01:18:40.031 --> 01:18:42.910
where it's straightforward explanations of

01:18:42.910 --> 01:18:45.300
here's what we're trying to do and why,

01:18:45.300 --> 01:18:47.830
a matter, here is what we like.

01:18:47.830 --> 01:18:50.470
We do a fair amount of public work too,

01:18:50.470 --> 01:18:53.120
trying to say we're exploring this world

01:18:53.120 --> 01:18:55.070
where people haven't been before,

01:18:55.070 --> 01:18:58.770
and it just opened up in
the last 30 years to us,

01:18:58.770 --> 01:19:00.564
and there's still a tremendous
amount we don't know,

01:19:00.564 --> 01:19:01.750
and we don't know what it feels like.

01:19:01.750 --> 01:19:03.140
Gravity doesn't matter.

01:19:03.140 --> 01:19:04.670
Capillary forces do.

01:19:04.670 --> 01:19:08.179
What are the other rules
we don't understand yet?

01:19:08.179 --> 01:19:11.610
And that, just saying why we do what we do

01:19:11.610 --> 01:19:14.193
ends up being really a
part of the conversation.

01:19:15.433 --> 01:19:16.420
